### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
### FinanceHQ – Obligations flow: manual Phase 3 checks
###   3.3 No token → 401
###   3.4 Empty list
###   3.5 Create RECURRING → 201
###   3.6 Create FIXED_TERM missing endDate → 400
###   3.7 Update amount → 200
### ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
### Prerequisites:
###   1. Server running on localhost:8080
###   2. Select "dev" environment (top-right in IntelliJ HTTP Client)
###   3. Run auth-flow.http Steps 1–2 first to populate accessToken
###   4. Run requests IN ORDER



### ─── 3.3: GET without token — expect 401 ────────
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/obligations


### ─── 3.4: GET with token — expect 200 [] ───────
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/obligations
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### ─── 3.5: POST RECURRING — expect 201 with id and nextDueDate ─
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/obligations
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Rent",
  "amount": 1500.00,
  "category": "ESSENTIAL",
  "period": "RECURRING",
  "paymentDay": 15
}

> {%
  client.global.set("obligationId", response.body.id);
%}


### ─── 3.6: POST FIXED_TERM missing endDate — expect 400 ProblemDetail ─
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/obligations
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Loan",
  "amount": 500.00,
  "category": "IMPORTANT",
  "period": "FIXED_TERM",
  "paymentDay": 10
}


### ─── 3.7: PATCH amount — expect 200 with updated amount ────
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/obligations/{{obligationId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 999.99
}
